tweet: 9. On accountability:  Jackman send a text message to his coach every day scoring how well his day went.

name: Justin Pintwala
tweet: 8. On designing the day: Jackman creates a daily design as if in the past tense of what the day has been.  At the end of the day he scores it & holds himself accountable to what he was trying to manifest or make happen.

name: Justin Pintwala
tweet: 7. On meditation:  Jackman practices Transcendental Meditatation. The TM mantra is saying to the monkey mind: I need you to climb to the top of that pole. And when you get to the top, I need you to climb back down. And when you get to the bottom, I need you to climb back up.

name: Justin Pintwala
tweet: 6. On the trick to life: The trick to life is not letting that (monkey mind) be your master, but let it be your servant".

name: Justin Pintwala
tweet: 5. On intuition: Jackman states: "There is some calling that is beyond the conscious brains strategizing of how to be happy and successful or meaningful in life. There is something elemental and instinctual".  The people he admires most hone that ability.

name: Justin Pintwala
tweet: 4. On clarity:  Jackman works with a coach to ask what it is he is here for, what it is he wants to do, having priorities very clearly set out so the turning points in your life can become clear.

name: Justin Pintwala
tweet: 3. On listening: Jackman stated: ‚ÄúOne thing, a consistent theme is that I listen to the messages.  They come in crazy ways.  They come in strange but clear concise ways"

name: Justin Pintwala
tweet: 2. On asking: First, instead of "thinking" about what to do, Jackman remembers constantly asking for what it is he is meant to do.

name: Justin Pintwala
tweet: 1. On fear of the wrong path:  Jackman had much more fear of being on the wrong path vs fear of failing at a path.
